{"questionId":"15123153","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the curve has a point of zero gradient at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> and a point of zero gradient at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempts to solve their <strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></strong> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is a point of zero gradient&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;The following two marks are independent of the first three marks.</p>\n<p>substitutes their expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</em></strong>is a point of zero gradient&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[5 marks]</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">substitutes either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;into their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is a point of zero gradient&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;<strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>The following two marks are independent of the first three marks.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">substitutes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>12</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;</em></strong>is a point of zero gradient&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[5 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15123153","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that the curve has a point of zero gradient at P0, b and a point of zero gradient at Q-23a,427a3+b.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}